UPDATE courses SET
    course_description = '<div class="wysiwyg prose line-clamp-14 overflow-hidden"><div><p>This course provides you with a wide variety of major and minor study areas to choose from based on your interests and career aspirations.</p><p>Apply for our Bachelor of Science and study a generalised first year, with the flexibility to choose from a wide range of double-majors from your second year onwards:</p><p><span style="font-size:14px;">Veterinary Bioscience</span></p><p>Focuses on the biological principles underlying animal health, behaviour and diseases. Prepares you for careers in veterinary sciences (following further study), animal production and nutrition, and animal research.</p><p style="font-weight: bold;"><span style="font-size:14px;">Wildlife and Ecosystem Conservation</span></p><p>Explores the preservation and management of wildlife and natural ecosystems. Equips you with knowledge to address biodiversity conservation, landscape rehabilitation and sustainability challenges.</p><p style="font-weight: bold;"><span style="font-size:14px;">Chemistry and Analytical Science</span></p><p>Combines the study of chemical processes with advanced analytical techniques. Prepares you for roles in research, industry and environmental monitoring.</p><p><span style="font-size:14px;">Brewing and Food Science</span></p><p>Centres on the science behind brewing, fermentation and food production. Offers pathways to careers in the food and beverage industries, including brewing innovation.</p><p style="font-weight: bold;"><span style="font-size:14px;">Geoscience</span></p><p>Examines Earth’s physical structure, materials and processes. Prepares you for work in environmental management, resource exploration and geological sciences.</p><p>Majors and minors</p><p>A wide variety of major and minor study areas are available:</p><p>• Biochemistry<br/>• Cell Biology Major<br/>• Chemistry<br/>• Ecology<br/>• Environmental restoration<br/>• Laboratory bioscience<br/>• Microbiology</p><p>